=head1 Procedure

  Part C: Multicast Neighbor Solicitation with the same SLLA
   17. TN1 transmits Packet A to the NUT.
   18. TN1 transmits Neighbor Advertisement B to the NUT after receiving any Neighbor Solicitations
        from the NUT
   19. Check the NCE of TN1 on the NUT and observe the packets transmitted by the NUT.
   20. Wait (DELAY_FIRST_PROBE_TIME) seconds.
   21. Check the NCE of TN1 on the NUT and observe the packets transmitted by the NUT.
   22. TN1 transmits Neighbor Solicitation D.
   23. TN1 transmits an Echo Request to the NUT.
   24. Check the NCE of TN1 on the NUT and observe the packets transmitted by the NUT.

=head1 Observable Results

  Part C

   Step 19:
   The NUT should update the NCE of TN1 to state STALE. After receiving the Echo
   Request from TN1, the NUT should send a Reply and enter state DELAY.

   Step 21:
   After DELAY_FIRST_PROBE_TIME, the NUT should transition to state PROBE
   by sending a unicast Neighbor Solicitation to TN1.

   Step 24:
   The NUT should not update the state of TN1's NCE after sending it's queued
   Neighbor Advertisement and Echo Reply and should stay in state PROBE. The NUT should
   retransmit its unicast Neighbor Solicitation to TN1.

=head1 Possible Problems

  * None.

